OL,6,FDuring video evidence at Swansea Crown
OL,7,FCourt on Tuesday, teacher Fiona Elias
OL,8,Fsaid she had told the teenage
OL,9,Fdefendant that she couldn't stay in a
OL,10,Flower school hall on the day of the
OL,11,Fattack.
OL,13,FMs Elias said the pupil had
OL,14,F"menacingly" stared at her while
OL,15,Fplaying with an object in her pocket.
OL,17,FIn the recorded police interview, Ms
OL,18,FElias said she had asked the defendant
OL,19,Fto stop staring at her and had asked
OL,20,Fher what was in her pocket.
